Systematic review of the two large periods in the history of psychology: (1) Before psychology was recognized as an independent field of knowledge, and (2) History of psychology proper which divides into two periods: philosophical psychology of Locke, Berkeley, Leibnitz and Kant, and emergence of experimental (or scientific)  psychology with the works of Wundt and Ebbinghaus.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Knowledge and critical evaluation of psychological fact, explanations and theories in their historical context.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  knowing historical facts; understanding historical and social context; critical thinking concerning psychological facts and theories; better ability to explain psychology for wider audiences.
